Since [[Pete Rose]] was banned from baseball, the Reds have not retired his #14. However, they have not reissued it except for [[Pete Rose, Jr.]] in his 11 game tenure in 1997.  
The number 11 of former captain [[Barry Larkin]] has not been issued since his retirement, and the Reds have not named a new captain since.

The following broadcasters are honored with microphones by the broadcast booth: [[Marty Brennaman]], [[Waite Hoyt]], and [[Joe Nuxhall]].&lt;ref&gt;See [[List of Major League Baseball retired numbers#Similar honors]].&lt;/ref&gt;

