The '''Central Powers''' ([[German language|German]]: '''''Mittelmächte'''''; [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]]: '''''Központi hatalmak'''''; [[Turkish language|Turkish]]: '''''İttifak Devletleri''''' or '''''Bağlaşma Devletleri'''''; [[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]]: '''''Централни сили''''') was one of the two sides that participated in [[World War I]] and was also known as the '''[[Triple Alliance (1882)|Triple Alliance]]''', the other being the [[Allies of World War I|Triple Entente (Allied Powers)]]. It was made up of the [[German Empire]], the [[Austria–Hungary|Austro-Hungarian Empire]], the [[Ottoman Empire]], and the [[Kingdom of Bulgaria]].

==Member states==
The Central Powers consisted of the [[German Empire]], the Austro-Hungarian Empire, the [[Ottoman Empire]], and the Kingdom of Bulgaria. The name &quot;Central Powers&quot; is derived from the location of these countries; all four were located between the [[Russian Empire]] in the east and [[French Third Republic|France]] and the [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]] in the west.

[[Image:World War 1.gif|thumb|300px|Allies and Central Powers in the First World War&lt;br&gt;{{color box|#088A08}} Allies&lt;br /&gt;{{color box|#01DF01}} Allied colonies, dominions, territories or occupied territory&lt;br&gt;{{color box|#FE9A2E}} Central powers&lt;br&gt;{{color box|#F7BE81}} Central powers colonies or occupied territory&lt;br&gt;{{color box|#BDBDBD}} Neutral countries]]
The Central Powers were composed of the following nations&lt;ref name=&quot;meyer&quot;&gt;{{cite book |title= A World Undone: The Story of the Great War, 1914 to 1918|last= Meyer|first= G.J.|year= 2007|publisher= Delta Trade Paperback|isbn= 0553382403}}&lt;/ref&gt;:
* {{flagicon|Austria-Hungary}} [[Austria–Hungary|Austro-Hungarian Empire]]: entered the war on 28 July 1914
* {{flag|German Empire}} (including [[German colonial empire|German colonial forces]]): 1 August 1914
* {{flag|Ottoman Empire}}: secretly 2 August 1914; openly 29 October 1914
* {{flagicon|Bulgaria}} [[Kingdom of Bulgaria]]: 14 October 1915

