'''Crank''' may refer to:

==Mechanism==
* [[Crank (mechanism)]], in mechanical engineering, a bent portion of an axle, or shaft, or an arm keyed at right angles to the end of a shaft, by which motion is imparted to or received from it
* [[Crankshaft]], the part of a piston engine which translates reciprocating linear piston motion into rotation
* [[Crankset]], the component of a bicycle drivetrain that converts the reciprocating motion of the rider's legs into rotational motion used to drive the chain, which in turn drives the rear wheel

==People==
* [[Anthony Crank]], a British television presenter
* [[Patrick Crank]], an American lawyer
* [[John Crank]] (1916-2006), a British mathematical physicist

==Places==
* [[Crank, Merseyside]], a village near Rainford, England

==Popular culture==
* [[Crank (film)|''Crank'' (film)]], a 2006 film starring Jason Statham
** ''[[Crank: High Voltage]]'', the 2009 sequel
* [[Crank (Hoodoo Gurus album)|''Crank'' (Hoodoo Gurus album)]], an album by the Australian rock group Hoodoo Gurus
* ''Crank'', an album by Scottish rock band [[The Almighty (band)|The Almighty]]
* [[Crank (novel)|''Crank'' (novel)]], a book written by Ellen Hopkins
* &quot;Crank&quot;, a song by [[Catherine Wheel]] off of their album ''Chrome''
* ''Crank'', an early 20th century [[periodical]]
* [[Crank! Records]], a record label that released albums by indie bands Mineral, The Gloria Record, and Bright Eyes

==Slang==
* [[Crank (person)]], a disparaging term for a person who holds an unorthodox opinion
* [[Prank call|Crank call]], a false telephone call
* Crank, slang term for powdered [[amphetamine]]s, especially [[methamphetamine]]
* Crank (action), a slang term for when a person has a cry during the act of [[masturbation]]

==Other==
* Crank conjecture, a term coined by Freeman Dyson to explain congruence patterns in [[Partition (number theory)|integer partitions]]
* [[Cranks restaurant]]

